headline: How Donald Trump is rewriting US history
subhead: As the country marks its 250th anniversary this year, the American president, who returned to the White House on January 20, 2025, has worked to shape a revised historical narrative, revealing signs of megalomania.

headline: PSG pound Marseille and move back to top of Ligue 1
subhead: Luis Enrique's Paris Saint-Germain, who beat Marseille 5-0 on Sunday, have now won seven straight league matches, though they remain under pressure from surprise challengers Lens, who sit just two points behind the PSG.

headline: French cosmetics sales drop in the US after being struck by tariffs
subhead: French production has struggled in the United States, its leading export market, amid competition from Korean brands.

headline: Mayor and mother: The young women changing France's local councils
subhead: Only 41 women under the age of 30 were elected as mayors in 2020, out of France's 34,885 mayors. Here are the stories of several women who have balanced their careers, motherhood and first terms in office in a political scene often dominated by older men.

headline: 'Canada, better the 28th EU member than the 51st US state'
subhead: The Canadian prime minister has called for an alliance of middle powers to stand up to the world's great powers. This is a compelling idea, and one that Europe has been pursuing for 60 years, writes Le Monde columnist Pascal Riché.

headline: Jacob Helberg, Trump's direct link to France's far right
subhead: Everyone in the French far right who wants to get close to Donald Trump knows that Jacob Helberg is the man to speak to. The French-American, a young under secretary of state for economic affairs, serves as a conduit for the reactionary, nationalist and anti-immigration vision that the president wants to impose on Europe.
